title: `__construct()`
description: Constructor.
...

~~~ .php.xmp
Elevator($input = [], $chunk = [5, 0], $path = true, $config = []); // @pages mode
Elevator($input = [], $current = "", $path = true, $config = []); // @page mode
~~~

**Example:**

~~~ .php
$elevator = new Elevator([0, 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7], [3, 0], 'foo/bar');
$elevator_str = $elevator . "";
~~~

Result:

~~~ .php
$elevator = [
    'up' => null,
    'hub' => 'foo/bar',
    'down' => 'foo/bar/2'
];
~~~

~~~ .php
$elevator_str = '<span>▲</span> <a href="foo/bar">◆</a> <a href="foo/bar/2">▼</a>';
~~~

To create horizontal elevator:

~~~ .php
$elevator = new Elevator([0, 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7], [3, 0], 'foo/bar', [
    'direction' => [
        '<' => 'previous', // ← default is `up`
        '>' => 'next' // ← default is `down`
    ],
    'union' => [
        // previous link
        '<' => [
            1 => '&#x25C0;' // union content
        ],
        // next link
        '>' => [
            1 => '&#x25B6;'
        ]
    ]
]);

$elevator_str = $elevator . "";
~~~

Result:

~~~ .php
$elevator = [
    'previous' => null,
    'hub' => 'foo/bar',
    'next' => 'foo/bar/2'
];
~~~

~~~ .php
$elevator_str = '<span>◀</span> <a href="foo/bar">◆</a> <a href="foo/bar/2">▶</a>';
~~~

